law.catch_line: Withholding information or giving false information.
law.text: No person shall willfully withhold information which will affect the rates or premiums chargeable under this subtitle from, or knowingly give false or misleading information to, the commissioner, any statistical agent, any advisory organization, or any insurer.
law.history: Amended 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 24, sec. 1135, effective July 15, 2010. -- Created 2000 Ky. Acts ch. 380, sec. 12, effective July 14, 2000.
